The paper discusses a distributed graph computing framework for processing large scale power-law graphs, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), social networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus is on graph processing and partitioning, cs.DC and cs.DB are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SI, cs.DS, and cs.LG.
